<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="overline">Our History</span>
      <h2>46 years of milestones</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="timeline">
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-date">1978</div>
        <h3>Founded in Houston</h3>
        <p>Dr. Eleanor Vance and James Ruiz establish Acme Chemical Company with 24 employees and one manufacturing line producing industrial surfactants.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-date">1984</div>
        <h3>Water Treatment Division Launch</h3>
        <p>Acme expands into water treatment chemistry, securing major contracts with Houston municipal water utilities and Gulf Coast petrochemical facilities.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-date">1991</div>
        <h3>First European Plant Opens</h3>
        <p>Acquisition of Chemwerk AG in Germany provides Acme with its first international manufacturing base and entry into European markets.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-date">1999</div>
        <h3>Pharmaceutical Division Established</h3>
        <p>Acme opens its first GMP-certified facility in New Jersey, marking entry into the pharmaceutical excipient and process chemical market.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-date">2006</div>
        <h3>Asia-Pacific Expansion</h3>
        <p>Joint venture with Jiangsu Petrochemical creates a 60,000-ton manufacturing hub in Nanjing, serving rapidly growing Asian electronics and automotive sectors.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-date">2014</div>
        <h3>Green Chemistry Initiative</h3>
        <p>Acme launches its Greenline platform — a commitment to developing bio-based and biodegradable alternatives across every product family.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-date">2019</div>
        <h3>Semiconductor Grade Launch</h3>
        <p>Opening of Acme's ISO Class 5 cleanroom facility in Hillsboro, Oregon — dedicated to ultra-high purity chemicals for semiconductor fabs.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="timeline-item">
        <div class="timeline-date">2024</div>
        <h3>Net-Zero Commitment</h3>
        <p>Acme announces a science-based net-zero target for 2040, backed by a $400M decarbonization investment program over 10 years.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

